HOUSE RESOLUTION 172
By Carringer
A RESOLUTION to honor and congratulate J.P. Payne on being
named District 3, Class 4A Coach of the Year in
boys' basketball.
WHEREAS, this legislative body takes great pleasure in recognizing those Tennesseans
who have distinguished themselves as great athletic coaches while motivating the young men
and women under their charge to reach for and attain the greatest heights; and
WHEREAS, J.P. Payne, first-year boys' basketball coach at Knoxville Central High
School, is most assuredly one such outstanding mentor; he quickly reversed the Bobcats'
fortunes during the 2025-2026 season and led his team to twenty-plus victories; and
WHEREAS, after Knoxville Central suffered through a losing season in 2024-2025, J.P.
Payne was hired as the Bobcats' new leader, and he quickly engineered a turnaround that
resulted in his team posting a perfect 8-0 record to claim the District 3, Class 4A regular season
championship for 2025-2026; and
WHEREAS, Coach Payne and the Bobcats then vanquished Knoxville Halls and
Knoxville West to win the District 3, Class 4A tournament title and advance to the regionals; and
WHEREAS, Coach Payne's inspiring leadership of the Knoxville Central Bobcats was
appropriately honored by his recognition as 2025-2026 District 3, Class 4A Coach of the Year in
boys' basketball; and
WHEREAS, Coach Payne has become a powerful force in only one year, and he is most
worthy of our approbation on this special occasion; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, that we honor and
congratulate J.P. Payne on being named District 3, Class 4A Coach of the Year in boys'
